cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with filter pruning in deep convolutional neural networks for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method for filter pruning, which falls under the category of machine learning algorithms, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of previous methods and analyzes the norm-based criterion, which involves mathematical concepts, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a relevant category. The paper also involves optimization techniques for model compression, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
